parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A crack in the engine block can cause oil leaks, engine failure, and potentially lead to engine seizure, resulting in loss of vehicle control and accidents.
A defective crankshaft can cause engine failure, leading to loss of vehicle control and accidents.
A failed camshaft balancer pulley can cause engine noise and potentially lead to engine failure.
A faulty TPS sensor can cause high idle, leading to decreased fuel efficiency and potentially causing accidents.
A failed upper engine hose can cause engine leaks, leading to engine failure and potentially causing accidents.
Oil pump failure can cause engine failure, leading to loss of vehicle control and accidents.
The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS does not perform satisfactorily
water comes into contact with electrical components affecting the ABS
the left rear brake locks up
premature wear on front brakes and tires

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Clunking Noise and Stiff Gear Shift
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clunking noise and stiff gear shift can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to difficulty shifting gears, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission makes a clunking noise when shifting into drive or reverse
hesitation or delay when shifting gears.
